snippet.textDisplay:
I feel like meltdown and spectre were put into the chips on purpose by Intel so that they could use it as an excuse for "planned obsolescence."  

We've reached a point where chips from 2013 are more than sufficient for any normal gamer's needs, and process shrinks are  becoming physically impossible, so real improvement in hardware is becoming difficult.  The only way to keep people buying new chips is to make the old ones obsolete with viruses.  

When spectre and meltdown were announced, they had never even been used to target a consumer PC, but we still had to take a performance hit anyway.  And now knowledge of the vulnerability is widespread, so people are starting to write code to target it on consumer PCs when they probably wouldn't have before.  Fucking intel...... 

My i7-3770k is probably going to be made obsolete on purpose through these performance hits so intel can sell me a new chip, just so i can have the same performance i used to have with the old chip.
